00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

2
00:00:06,640 --> 00:00:08,399
{\an8}- Yes.
- All right.

3
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:10,439
{\an8}- And you're taking your time.
- Peace be upon you.

4
00:00:10,440 --> 00:00:12,559
{\an8}- And peace be upon you too.
- What are you cooking?

5
00:00:12,560 --> 00:00:13,999
{\an8}It smells so good.

6
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,200
{\an8}Radwa.

7
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:17,320
{\an8}I missed you.

8
00:00:26,840 --> 00:00:29,119
{\an8}If I can't have Ridz,

9
00:00:29,120 --> 00:00:30,760
{\an8}neither can you.

10
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:33,400
{\an8}What's going on?

11
00:00:34,040 --> 00:00:35,679
{\an8}- Oh my God!
- Aina, what have you done?

12
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,599
{\an8}Oh my God.

13
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:38,920
{\an8}Aina!

14
00:00:52,440 --> 00:00:53,680
Are you okay?

15
00:00:54,640 --> 00:00:55,799
Yes.

16
00:00:55,800 --> 00:00:57,360
I'm okay.

17
00:00:58,080 --> 00:00:59,200
Dear.

18
00:00:59,840 --> 00:01:00,720
Yes?

19
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:03,280
Will Aina and Auntie be there later?

20
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:07,840
As far as I know, I didn't invite them.

21
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:11,040
Okay.

22
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:13,080
Okay?

23
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:16,800
All right, wear your seatbelt.

24
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,559
Grandma!

25
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:33,039
Ridz is here!

26
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:35,759
{\an8}- Grandma, peace be upon you!
- And peace be upon you.

27
00:01:35,760 --> 00:01:37,640
{\an8}My dear granddaughter!

28
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:41,799
Grandma, presenting

29
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:45,640
the proposal entourage
for your beloved granddaughter.

30
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:49,399
Proposal, huh?

31
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:52,000
You're suddenly getting married.

32
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,759
You didn't even give me a heads-up.

33
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:56,479
Sorry, Grandma.

34
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:59,159
Let me introduce Haider,

35
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:02,200
who has captured
your granddaughter's heart.

36
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:04,919
- He's the one who wanted to get married.
- Yes.

37
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:07,479
- Scold him instead.
- Grandma, are you well?

38
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:09,839
Praise God, I'm well.

39
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:12,639
Be patient. This is normal.

40
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:14,959
She loves to mess around.

41
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:18,160
- Peace be upon you, Grandma.
- And peace be upon you.

42
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:20,199
I missed you very much.

43
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:22,599
Sorry for showing up all of a sudden.

44
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:26,959
It's okay. I'm glad you are here.

45
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:28,519
How are you?

46
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:29,919
Praise God, I am fine.

47
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:32,120
- How are you?
- I'm fine.

48
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:34,200
Are you doing well?

49
00:02:41,160 --> 00:02:42,280
Radwa!

50
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:46,400
Radwa, I want to apologize
for the other day.

51
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,600
I didn't do it on purpose.

52
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:56,200
Darling.

53
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:59,400
- What's wrong with you?
- Why did you push Aina?

54
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:02,439
Look, get up. The floor is dirty.

55
00:03:02,440 --> 00:03:05,159
For your information,
it was because of this woman.

56
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:08,439
She's the reason we were kicked out
of Tiana's house that day.

57
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:10,599
Yes, Grandma. That's right.

58
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:13,480
I've heard more bad things
than good, Grandma.

59
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:16,239
Is this true, Ridz?

60
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:18,079
Grandma, of course it's true.
Why wouldn't it be?

61
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:20,759
That day, Aina slandered Radwa
about wanting to kill her.

62
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:22,079
She even put a needle in the cake.

63
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:24,519
That's why Mom and Dad went berserk.

64
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:26,280
Maybe she even faked her fall.

65
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,759
You and your nonsense.

66
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:33,479
That's enough.
I've prepared a few dishes today.

67
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:35,559
I cooked, so come in.

68
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:38,159
Come on in. Don't just stand around.

69
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:40,159
Radwa, for your information,

70
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:43,400
Alia, Aina's sister,

71
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:45,520
has a rather strange husband.

72
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:47,800
It's your first time here, right?

73
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:51,119
It's better not to come here.

74
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:53,400
They're all the same.

75
00:03:54,160 --> 00:03:57,159
Okay. Dear, let's go inside.

76
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:58,800
Let's go!

77
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:01,000
Come on, Ridz!

78
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:07,879
Dear God.

79
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:10,079
Forgive my sins, dear God.

80
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:12,000
And the sins of my wife.

81
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,960
Please protect my wife and our marriage.

82
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,680
Amen.

83
00:04:19,279 --> 00:04:22,000
Radwa, I want to apologize
for the other day.

84
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:26,280
Your sister said you can't have children.

85
00:04:26,960 --> 00:04:31,000
Just wait until Ridz divorces you.

86
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:37,599
Amen.

87
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:39,440
What are you thinking about?

88
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,040
Come on, tell me.

89
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:46,959
It's nothing.

90
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:48,240
I'm just a little tired.

91
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:51,720
Darling.

92
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,280
I'm sorry

93
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:58,479
about Auntie and Aina.

94
00:04:58,480 --> 00:05:01,080
I didn't know they were here.

95
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:06,439
If you're uncomfortable,
we'll pack our things and book a hotel.

96
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:08,719
Don't. It's okay here.

97
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,560
Don't waste money.

98
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:14,319
I'm okay. Don't worry.

99
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:16,080
Of course I'll worry.

100
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:19,000
I know what happened earlier.

101
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:22,040
Nothing happened.

102
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:24,440
Enough. Don't think about Aina, okay?

103
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:27,639
Let's eat.

104
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:28,960
I'm hungry.

105
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:32,040
Okay.

106
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:34,240
Sure?

107
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:38,000
Okay, come on.

108
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:45,759
Have some sambal.

109
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:47,600
I cooked this.

110
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:50,560
So have you bought everything?

111
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:54,040
Everything is settled except for the cake.

112
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:56,840
Good.

113
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:59,919
The guest list is done, right?

114
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:03,199
I invited Dad, Mom and Thaufiq.

115
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:04,640
But Thaufiq is out of town.

116
00:06:05,880 --> 00:06:08,279
So it's just Dad, Mom and you.

117
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:10,040
Just a small group for the solemnization.

118
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,079
- Haider?
- I was thinking

119
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:15,919
of inviting my friends and superiors.

120
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:17,760
Around 50 people.

121
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:19,439
You're thinking about it?

122
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:20,640
What's there to think about?

123
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:22,440
Fifty?

124
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:25,079
What? That's too many.

125
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:28,240
Thalia, you're already raising your voice?

126
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:32,479
That's enough. Just accept it.

127
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:34,359
As you wish!

128
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:36,039
I'm full.

129
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:37,800
Why is she upset?

130
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:40,999
- This girl...
- I'll check on Thalia.

131
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,559
Yes, go on.

132
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:45,079
- Everyone is still eating.
- Kids these days.

133
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:46,160
Stubborn.

134
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:48,360
How can she be a wife?

135
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,719
She always does as she pleases.
It's suffocating.

136
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:54,360
Why are you bothered by what she's doing?

137
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,359
Whose child is this?

138
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:07,479
It's Mrs. Farida's grandchild
from next door.

139
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:10,479
She asked me to look after her.

140
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:12,480
This is Laila.

141
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:15,080
She has to attend a lecture
at the mosque tonight.

142
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,959
Aina loves kids, Mom.

143
00:07:18,960 --> 00:07:20,120
Just like Ridz.

144
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,760
Do you want to hold her?

145
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:34,159
She likes you, dear.

146
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:35,919
Come to me.

147
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:37,000
Radwa.

148
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:39,920
This baby isn't used to strangers.

149
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:42,239
So if you want to hold one,

150
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:44,800
you need to have your own child.

151
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:47,360
Only if that's possible.

152
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:52,239
What's the point of having a wife
if she can't get pregnant?

153
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,839
Right.

154
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:57,279
Ridz has always loved kids.

155
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:58,919
But pity him.

156
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:01,079
He has a barren wife.

157
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:03,440
Since when was there
a doctor in this house?

158
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:07,880
Are you a doctor talking about my wife?

159
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:12,479
That's enough, darling. Come on.

160
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:13,999
It stinks here.

161
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,000
There are many spiteful people here.
Come on, darling.

162
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:18,160
Can you move aside?

163
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:31,159
- Are you okay?
- No!

164
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:33,200
You know I don't want a big reception.

165
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:36,439
Well, you chose the solemnization venue.

166
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,519
Let me invite my friends.

167
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:39,919
Meet me halfway.

168
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:42,678
Are you saying I don't?

169
00:08:42,679 --> 00:08:46,040
No, I prefer a lively reception.

170
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:49,399
- Give me a chance.
- Give you a chance?

171
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:51,799
Okay. Invite everyone.

172
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:55,239
Invite everyone,
even the woman from the next village,

173
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:57,039
the gravedigger, and even stray cats.

174
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:58,120
Make the occasion lively!

175
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:05,800
What a mess!

176
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:10,000
Surely, you want children, right?

177
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:15,080
Don't think about all that, darling.

178
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:20,880
But they're right.

179
00:09:25,680 --> 00:09:27,880
It has only been six months
since we got married.

180
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:32,360
A child is the last thing on my mind.

181
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:36,120
Because all of that is God's will.

182
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:44,000
But what if I really can't get pregnant?

183
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:47,320
Or if I never have children?

184
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:50,680
Will you be okay?

185
00:09:58,760 --> 00:10:00,160
Look at me.

186
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:03,320
Face me.

187
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:08,160
Darling.

188
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:12,440
God has laid out our path.

189
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:18,080
I'll come to terms with
whether we have children or not.

190
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:20,680
I'll still be happy.

191
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:27,440
Now,

192
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:31,600
let me focus on you.

193
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:36,040
Let me pamper you.

194
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:42,159
When we do have children,
I'm afraid you will have

195
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:45,440
a hard time juggling
between me and the baby.

196
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:48,480
So now,

197
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:52,040
let me spend time with you.

198
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:55,120
Can I?

199
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:59,760
You're so full of it.

200
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:03,359
Okay, I'm going to get water.

201
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:04,800
I'm thirsty.

202
00:11:33,880 --> 00:11:35,400
You're sighing deeply.

203
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:39,880
Don't overthink what they said earlier.

204
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:42,440
They're just talking nonsense.

205
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:45,479
I'm Airil.

206
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:47,480
You can call me dear Airil.

207
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:51,480
It's better for you not to get pregnant.

208
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:55,439
When you get pregnant
and your body changes,

209
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:56,840
you won't be pretty anymore.

210
00:12:02,880 --> 00:12:05,400
Hey, my hands don't have poison.

211
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,560
Where are you going in such a hurry?

212
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,559
Please, move aside.

213
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:14,560
I'm going to my room.

214
00:12:19,520 --> 00:12:20,720
Make a drink for me.

215
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,040
Just a simple one.

216
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:26,720
A <i>tongkat ali</i> coffee will do.

217
00:12:33,280 --> 00:12:35,000
It's okay if you can't.

218
00:12:36,040 --> 00:12:38,600
I can't even ask for a small favor.

219
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:49,480
The coffee is in the bottom cabinet.

220
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:59,559
Oh, yes! I just remembered.

221
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:01,439
Coffee is up there.

222
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:03,200
Grandma put it there.

223
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,560
Never mind, I'll help.

224
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:35,159
Darling, what's wrong?

225
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:38,119
- Nothing.
- Why is your face red?

226
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:39,680
I'm okay.

227
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:41,559
Darling.

228
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:43,999
Dear, I want to ask again.

229
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,839
If I really cannot get pregnant,

230
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:49,199
- will you leave me--
- Wait.

231
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,920
What are you saying?

232
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:54,279
You're always overthinking.
I already told you.

233
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:56,040
Don't think too much.

234
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,520
Dear.

235
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:11,080
Have Airil and Alia been married for long?

236
00:14:13,280 --> 00:14:15,039
Yes.

237
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:16,480
But they have no kids.

238
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:20,280
What's the matter, darling?

239
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:22,839
Did Airil harass you?

240
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:24,639
No.

241
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:26,120
Dear, let's go to bed.

242
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:28,520
I'm going to the bathroom.

243
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:47,040
Darling.

244
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:50,080
Are you okay?

245
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:53,680
Yes, I'm okay.

246
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,720
Are you sure?

247
00:14:58,600 --> 00:14:59,640
I'm fine.

248
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:05,480
Let's go and eat.

249
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:09,200
I don't want to.

250
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:13,720
Do you not want to go on a date with me?

251
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:26,559
Darling.

252
00:15:26,560 --> 00:15:27,920
If possible,

253
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:30,120
I want to be like that chicken.

254
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:33,239
You want to become a chicken?

255
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:35,480
You can't. It's a sin.

256
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:39,160
Why is it a sin?

257
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:42,919
Gosh, my wife is dense.

258
00:15:42,920 --> 00:15:44,639
She's also a bit slow.

259
00:15:44,640 --> 00:15:46,799
- Say that again.
- Okay, no.

260
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:48,679
I mean I don't want to be a chicken.

261
00:15:48,680 --> 00:15:51,999
I want to be like chicken
because it cheers you up

262
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:54,599
when you're sad, angry or crying.

263
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:57,440
You're happy when you eat chicken.
So I want to be like one.

264
00:16:01,880 --> 00:16:04,199
Are you stingy?
You don't want to buy me fried chicken.

265
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:06,080
Are you saving money?

266
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:11,280
Saving? I can afford
plenty of chicken with my salary.

267
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:19,720
Darling.

268
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:22,680
Can I ask you something?

269
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:26,200
Sure.

270
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:31,160
What happened at home yesterday?

271
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:36,760
Nothing.

272
00:16:37,520 --> 00:16:39,160
Last night?

273
00:16:41,080 --> 00:16:42,160
Nothing as well.

274
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:44,400
Don't lie.

275
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:48,240
I'm not lying. I cannot lie.

276
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:50,720
Lying to your husband is a sin.

277
00:16:54,360 --> 00:16:55,879
Darling.

278
00:16:55,880 --> 00:16:58,439
Tell me if you have something to say.

279
00:16:58,440 --> 00:17:01,040
There should be no secrets between us.

280
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:03,920
Okay? Promise me that.

281
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:08,280
- We'll see.
- Promise.

282
00:17:14,839 --> 00:17:16,200
Thank you.

283
00:17:25,079 --> 00:17:26,759
I'm sorry.

284
00:17:26,760 --> 00:17:28,679
I've thought it through.

285
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:30,719
I agree to have a small wedding.

286
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:32,559
The important part is getting married.

287
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:33,919
Are you sure?

288
00:17:33,920 --> 00:17:35,360
Yes.

289
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:37,479
In that case, I want to apologize too

290
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:39,960
because I got emotional and scolded you.

291
00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:42,439
You're cute when you're mad.

292
00:17:42,440 --> 00:17:44,960
- I'm cute when I'm mad?
- Talking back now?

293
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:48,960
This is done.

294
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:52,200
- Did you make a lot?
- Just a bit more, Grandma.

295
00:17:53,560 --> 00:17:56,559
The event crew asked

296
00:17:56,560 --> 00:17:58,680
if you want to sit on the dais.

297
00:17:59,440 --> 00:18:02,319
If so, they want to give
a discount for the dais.

298
00:18:02,320 --> 00:18:04,520
No need for a dais, Grandma.
It'll be too much.

299
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:08,480
Why? You only get married
once in your life.

300
00:18:09,520 --> 00:18:12,560
Sure, you only get married once,
but a simple gathering is enough.

301
00:18:14,240 --> 00:18:16,080
I want a reception.

302
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:18,119
Calm down.

303
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:19,839
As you wish.

304
00:18:19,840 --> 00:18:21,159
But I don't want it.

305
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:24,559
So are we just taking photos
at the dining table later?

306
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:27,399
There will be prawns
on the pineapple display tray.

307
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:30,399
And the photos will show leftovers.

308
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:31,879
- Is that what you want?
- No.

309
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:33,599
Not that way.

310
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:35,920
- But...
- But?

311
00:18:36,440 --> 00:18:38,199
No exceptions, Haider.

312
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:40,319
You're always doing what you want.

313
00:18:40,320 --> 00:18:42,639
We only get married once in our lives.

314
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:45,319
The same goes for you.
You always do what you want!

315
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:48,119
- I've given in too many times.
- Did you say give in?

316
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:49,679
So what about me?

317
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:50,959
You wanted to get married earlier.

318
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:52,400
You're afraid
you'll be going for an operation.

319
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:54,559
I'm following your wish.

320
00:18:54,560 --> 00:18:56,639
Do you think I want to get married
in haste like this?

321
00:18:56,640 --> 00:18:59,679
Not hastily.
Why are you getting emotional, Thalia?

322
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:01,199
What did you say?

323
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:04,559
If I'm emotional,
go out and find an unemotional woman!

324
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:07,399
I'm troublesome
and I don't tolerate you, is that it?

325
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:10,000
Find another woman
because I don't want to marry you!

326
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:11,959
What are you saying?

327
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:14,720
I'm saying this wedding is canceled!

328
00:19:16,480 --> 00:19:17,560
This girl...

329
00:19:30,760 --> 00:19:32,760
- Can I come in?
- Sure.

330
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:39,960
Are you packing to go back to KL?

331
00:19:47,840 --> 00:19:49,999
Radwa, when I think again,

332
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,999
I don't know Haider at all.

333
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:54,080
How am I going to marry him?

334
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:57,159
True.

335
00:19:57,160 --> 00:19:59,159
If we don't know that person,

336
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:00,720
or what they want,

337
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:02,639
how can we live with them?

338
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:04,799
Yes and we're always arguing.

339
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:06,919
We both want different things.

340
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:09,600
How can we get married
when we're not compatible at all?

341
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:13,879
The problem isn't compatibility.

342
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:16,000
She doesn't tolerate anything at all.

343
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:18,799
Here's the thing, Haider.

344
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:20,640
Communication is very important.

345
00:20:21,320 --> 00:20:24,079
You have to always discuss and share.

346
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:26,719
The most important part is to be honest.

347
00:20:26,720 --> 00:20:28,719
- Don't keep secrets.
- Right.

348
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:31,439
But not her.
Does she think I can read her mind?

349
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:33,839
I'm not expecting him to read my mind.

350
00:20:33,840 --> 00:20:38,640
If he truly knows me, he'll understand
without me saying anything.

351
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:42,079
That's true.
We can't tell them everything.

352
00:20:42,080 --> 00:20:44,319
We don't have to tell everything, right?

353
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:45,720
Yes.

354
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,720
It's not that I don't love Haider.

355
00:20:49,320 --> 00:20:52,839
But if we argue like this every day,

356
00:20:52,840 --> 00:20:54,759
how can we get married?

357
00:20:54,760 --> 00:20:56,800
We get married to be happy.

358
00:21:03,280 --> 00:21:04,680
Be happy?

359
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:08,679
Of course we get married to be happy.

360
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:11,840
But she has to be fair.
Let me win sometimes.

361
00:21:15,560 --> 00:21:16,920
I...

362
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:19,679
Actually, I don't like you
marrying my elder sister.

363
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:21,399
You understand why, right?

364
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:23,480
But deep down...

365
00:21:24,160 --> 00:21:26,000
I feel really relieved.

366
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:30,000
I'm relieved you're the only one
who can take care of my elder sister.

367
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:33,360
With that, I have one piece
of advice for you.

368
00:21:34,880 --> 00:21:35,759
What is it?

369
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,680
The key to happiness

370
00:21:38,560 --> 00:21:39,960
isn't tolerance,

371
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:42,400
but yielding.

372
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:47,559
As a husband, you must give in.

373
00:21:47,560 --> 00:21:48,920
Okay?

374
00:21:49,520 --> 00:21:51,120
That's strange advice.

375
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:54,560
Who's the one who's already married?

376
00:21:56,640 --> 00:21:58,960
You're making that face.

377
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:01,800
- You're making that face again.
- Are you speaking in an accent?

378
00:22:03,040 --> 00:22:04,000
Don't ask.

379
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:06,120
Do you want me to slap you?

380
00:22:06,840 --> 00:22:08,520
Don't be stubborn with me.

381
00:22:10,320 --> 00:22:12,360
- Okay.
- You'll understand when you get married.

382
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:19,839
Where are Thalia, Haider and Aina?

383
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:22,039
Thalia is in her room.

384
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:23,800
Haider went out for a while.
Let him cool down.

385
00:22:25,640 --> 00:22:28,079
Peace be upon you.

386
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:30,519
And peace be upon you.

387
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:33,719
Why do you always bring this baby over?

388
00:22:33,720 --> 00:22:36,520
Maybe Aina is babysitting
part-time, Grandma.

389
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,959
You're funny.

390
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:41,040
It's not funny!

391
00:22:42,240 --> 00:22:44,999
- That's insolent.
- Is it really, Mom?

392
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:46,240
I laughed.

393
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:51,160
Ridz.

394
00:22:53,960 --> 00:22:55,759
I'm not doing this part-time, Grandma.

395
00:22:55,760 --> 00:22:59,600
But Laila misses Uncle Ridz.

396
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:02,519
Poor Ridz.

397
00:23:02,520 --> 00:23:03,800
He can't have children of his own.

398
00:23:09,480 --> 00:23:10,520
Darling, hold her for a while.

399
00:23:11,160 --> 00:23:12,560
I'm going to wash my hands.

400
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:28,760
Why are you whispering?

401
00:23:32,240 --> 00:23:33,600
Look at that, Mom.

402
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:37,559
She's holding the baby like a doll.

403
00:23:37,560 --> 00:23:39,919
It's a good thing she's barren.

404
00:23:39,920 --> 00:23:42,560
The child would die
if she had one of her own.

405
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:46,679
Right, Mom.
People get married to have children.

406
00:23:46,680 --> 00:23:49,360
Maybe she married because of lust.

407
00:23:50,280 --> 00:23:52,640
I'm just respecting Grandma here.

408
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:56,360
Don't undermine me.

409
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:59,519
Jeez, she's just kidding.

410
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:01,479
No need to be upset.

411
00:24:01,480 --> 00:24:02,840
Right, Radwa?

412
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:04,679
Just kidding?

413
00:24:04,680 --> 00:24:06,880
There's a limit to joking around.

414
00:24:21,440 --> 00:24:23,520
Well, look at that! How insolent.

415
00:24:25,320 --> 00:24:27,760
- I seek forgiveness from God.
- Take this baby.

416
00:24:29,120 --> 00:24:31,000
Don't show your brainless attitude here.

417
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:39,320
Darling.

418
00:24:41,880 --> 00:24:42,920
Did Airil bother you?

419
00:24:43,880 --> 00:24:45,880
No.

420
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:49,639
Go to the room and rest.

421
00:24:49,640 --> 00:24:51,919
- But I haven't washed the dishes.
- Let me do it.

422
00:24:51,920 --> 00:24:54,359
It's okay. Go to the room and rest.

423
00:24:54,360 --> 00:24:56,200
Please.

424
00:25:17,960 --> 00:25:19,039
- Radwa.
- What's this?

425
00:25:19,040 --> 00:25:22,000
- Where are you going?
- Let go!

426
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:25,479
The more you refuse,

427
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:27,999
- the more I like it.
- Move it!

428
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:29,360
What's with you?

429
00:25:30,360 --> 00:25:31,960
Dear!

430
00:25:34,800 --> 00:25:37,280
You're very pretty.

431
00:25:38,160 --> 00:25:39,680
Not suitable for Ridz at all.

432
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:43,600
You should find a man
more compatible with you.

433
00:25:44,960 --> 00:25:46,400
Dear!

434
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:53,000
What are you doing, asshole?

435
00:25:56,320 --> 00:25:58,720
What are you doing?

436
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:01,039
Do you want to die?

437
00:26:01,040 --> 00:26:03,999
Enough. Why are you doing this
to someone else's child?

438
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:06,199
- Oh my God!
- Ridz, stop it!

439
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:08,359
- Let him die!
- Dear?

440
00:26:08,360 --> 00:26:10,440
Dear, please stop it!

441
00:26:11,080 --> 00:26:12,080
Dear.

442
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:14,160
Take your husband out of here.

443
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:18,319
Get out of my house!

444
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:20,119
I don't want to see you ever again!

445
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:22,520
- Leave!
- Enough. Alia!

446
00:26:23,080 --> 00:26:24,200
Go back.

447
00:26:25,520 --> 00:26:26,680
I said go back!

448
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:32,199
Dear.

449
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:33,920
Are you mad at me?

450
00:26:36,640 --> 00:26:38,000
Dear.

451
00:26:40,240 --> 00:26:42,400
- Dear, please say something.
- No.

452
00:26:43,760 --> 00:26:46,719
I'm not mad at you, but at myself.

453
00:26:46,720 --> 00:26:49,680
I feel like I've failed you.

454
00:26:50,560 --> 00:26:52,359
No, it's not your fault.

455
00:26:52,360 --> 00:26:54,999
It's all my fault
for not telling you earlier.

456
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:57,480
Why didn't you tell me?

457
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:00,759
- Don't you trust me?
- No.

458
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:04,279
No. I didn't want you
to fight with your family.

459
00:27:04,280 --> 00:27:05,680
That's all.

460
00:27:06,320 --> 00:27:08,360
Dear, I'm so sorry.

461
00:27:15,040 --> 00:27:17,360
From now on, promise me

462
00:27:19,360 --> 00:27:21,440
you won't keep secrets from me. Okay?

463
00:27:24,640 --> 00:27:26,160
Are you okay?

464
00:27:26,840 --> 00:27:28,320
I'm okay.

465
00:27:31,160 --> 00:27:32,400
I'm sorry, my treasure.

466
00:27:34,560 --> 00:27:36,040
I'm sorry.

467
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:02,160
Dear.

468
00:28:02,960 --> 00:28:04,320
Yes.

469
00:28:08,280 --> 00:28:10,319
I can't live without you.

470
00:28:10,320 --> 00:28:13,439
The past two days
have been frustrating for me.

471
00:28:13,440 --> 00:28:16,079
I don't know how to live without you.

472
00:28:16,080 --> 00:28:18,879
We're not compatible, Haider.

473
00:28:18,880 --> 00:28:20,559
You're north and I'm south.

474
00:28:20,560 --> 00:28:22,760
You want black and I want white.

475
00:28:23,920 --> 00:28:26,960
We can't be arguing like this
throughout our marriage.

476
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:30,960
I apologize for always opposing you.

477
00:28:31,760 --> 00:28:35,719
I promise to follow everything after this.

478
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:38,079
This isn't about opposing.

479
00:28:38,080 --> 00:28:40,359
We, you and I...

480
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:42,679
are not compatible. Understood?

481
00:28:42,680 --> 00:28:45,959
I don't want to be the reason
you don't get what you want in life.

482
00:28:45,960 --> 00:28:47,480
We're too different.

483
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:50,919
Never mind, I'm willing to give in.

484
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:52,879
- How long will you give in?
- Forever.

485
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:54,559
You're crazy!

486
00:28:54,560 --> 00:28:57,320
I'm crazy. Crazy about you.

487
00:29:00,480 --> 00:29:04,320
If compatibility matters to you,
we'll go and check.

488
00:29:05,800 --> 00:29:07,280
Check?

489
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:09,600
What is there to check?

490
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:14,120
We'll check.

491
00:29:18,560 --> 00:29:21,479
Okay, Thalia. Close your eyes.

492
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:25,480
I'll go and choose the cake you like.

493
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:29,080
If I get it right,
you won't have to doubt anymore.

494
00:29:30,280 --> 00:29:33,079
You'll definitely like it.

495
00:29:33,080 --> 00:29:35,040
- For sure.
- Okay.

496
00:29:35,680 --> 00:29:38,079
- Agree?
- We can't. We're not married yet.

497
00:29:38,080 --> 00:29:40,119
Agree. I'll close my eyes.

498
00:29:40,120 --> 00:29:42,039
But make sure it's correct.

499
00:29:42,040 --> 00:29:44,879
Don't waste my effort
of coming here, okay?

500
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:46,519
Yes, I promise not to waste it.

501
00:29:46,520 --> 00:29:48,480
- Promise.
- Okay? One, two, three.

502
00:29:56,160 --> 00:29:57,680
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

503
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:07,120
Hold on.

504
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:21,319
Okay, done.

505
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:22,920
Open your eyes.
You've had them closed for a while.

506
00:30:23,520 --> 00:30:25,359
No, I'm afraid you got it wrong.

507
00:30:25,360 --> 00:30:27,079
Okay, on the count of three.

508
00:30:27,080 --> 00:30:29,599
I'll count and open my eyes, okay?

509
00:30:29,600 --> 00:30:32,880
- One, two, three.
- One, two, three.

510
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:36,039
- Correct!
- Correct?

511
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:39,199
I told you we're compatible.

512
00:30:39,200 --> 00:30:40,760
Right?

513
00:30:41,840 --> 00:30:43,399
I love you.

514
00:30:43,400 --> 00:30:45,360
What? What did you say?

515
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:48,480
- I love you?
- You love me?

516
00:30:49,120 --> 00:30:50,999
Thalia, I love you too.

517
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:52,479
Let's get married.

518
00:30:52,480 --> 00:30:54,639
Next time. We'll wait.

519
00:30:54,640 --> 00:30:55,760
We need a date.

520
00:30:56,360 --> 00:30:58,599
- But we're getting married?
- Yes.

521
00:30:58,600 --> 00:31:00,279
Okay, eat up.

522
00:31:00,280 --> 00:31:02,080
We'll get married.

523
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:21,560
Hey, barren woman!

524
00:32:22,160 --> 00:32:24,879
You came here and ruined my family.

525
00:32:24,880 --> 00:32:27,439
You seduced Alia's husband, right?

526
00:32:27,440 --> 00:32:29,919
Be silent if you know nothing.

527
00:32:29,920 --> 00:32:31,599
Don't harass me.

528
00:32:31,600 --> 00:32:34,360
I want you to divorce Ridz!

529
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:40,320
Even if we get divorced,
there's no guarantee he wants you.

530
00:32:41,680 --> 00:32:45,879
You need to understand
that it takes two to tango.

531
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:48,360
Snap to your senses.

532
00:32:50,680 --> 00:32:53,320
You don't deserve Ridz.

533
00:32:54,720 --> 00:32:56,400
You're barren!

534
00:32:57,920 --> 00:33:00,400
Is that all you have against me?

535
00:33:03,520 --> 00:33:08,000
Do you know Ridz was destined
to be with me since childhood?

536
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:10,440
I was supposed to marry him!

537
00:33:11,120 --> 00:33:15,360
But you appeared suddenly
and stole him from me!

538
00:33:17,080 --> 00:33:19,120
You're crazy.

539
00:33:20,840 --> 00:33:22,680
Don't disturb me.

540
00:33:26,240 --> 00:33:27,560
Aina!

541
00:33:28,960 --> 00:33:30,839
Aina!

542
00:33:30,840 --> 00:33:32,120
Stop it, Aina!

543
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:38,640
Aina, have you lost your mind?

544
00:33:39,240 --> 00:33:41,999
You drove me crazy.

545
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:44,119
Don't!

546
00:33:44,120 --> 00:33:45,760
Don't hit me!

547
00:33:46,880 --> 00:33:47,839
What's going on?

548
00:33:47,840 --> 00:33:49,599
It hurts!

549
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:51,199
What did you do to my daughter?

550
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:53,800
She slapped me.

551
00:33:55,120 --> 00:33:57,479
Radwa, did you slap Aina?

552
00:33:57,480 --> 00:34:00,319
No, Grandma. I swear, I didn't.

553
00:34:00,320 --> 00:34:02,679
Oh dear. Why, child?

554
00:34:02,680 --> 00:34:05,679
You don't deserve Ridz!

555
00:34:05,680 --> 00:34:07,679
You don't deserve to marry him either!

556
00:34:07,680 --> 00:34:10,439
- Insolent!
- You're mad!

557
00:34:10,440 --> 00:34:14,040
What's with you?
Just marry Ridz to someone else!

558
00:34:14,960 --> 00:34:17,638
Ridz is in the uniformed services,
so he can't practice polygamy.

559
00:34:17,639 --> 00:34:21,399
But he must divorce this barren woman!

560
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:23,678
- Just divorce her!
- Divorce.

561
00:34:23,679 --> 00:34:27,760
Then let him marry someone
who can give him children.

562
00:34:28,600 --> 00:34:31,119
- Ridz wants children!
- Enough!

563
00:34:31,120 --> 00:34:32,559
Enough!

564
00:34:32,560 --> 00:34:34,040
Oh my God.

565
00:34:46,600 --> 00:34:49,678
<i>Ridz is in the uniformed services,
so he can't practice polygamy.</i>

566
00:34:49,679 --> 00:34:53,039
<i>But he must divorce this barren woman!</i>

567
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:54,719
<i>Just divorce her!</i>

568
00:34:56,199 --> 00:35:01,320
<i>Then let him marry someone
who can give him children.</i>

569
00:35:05,600 --> 00:35:08,720
Come to me, sweetie.

570
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:13,000
You wouldn't need to hold my child
if you had your own.

571
00:35:13,640 --> 00:35:16,280
Don't say that.
Radwa will be hurt if she hears that.

572
00:35:17,720 --> 00:35:19,240
I was just kidding.

573
00:35:21,040 --> 00:35:23,920
If possible, I don't want
to hold someone else's child.

574
00:35:25,920 --> 00:35:28,200
I want to experience having my own child.

575
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:31,800
But that's the thing. I...

576
00:35:32,840 --> 00:35:34,520
I don't want to pressure Radwa.

577
00:36:04,760 --> 00:36:07,000
Don't.

578
00:36:13,120 --> 00:36:14,760
It's fine if we do.

579
00:36:15,760 --> 00:36:18,000
It's okay if we don't.
By God's grace, I'll be okay.

580
00:36:19,760 --> 00:36:22,200
Who are we to question God's will?

581
00:36:23,880 --> 00:36:25,040
Right?

582
00:36:25,960 --> 00:36:28,479
Ridz, what about Radwa?

583
00:36:28,480 --> 00:36:30,400
Is she still traumatized
from that incident with the heart?

584
00:36:31,960 --> 00:36:33,400
I don't know.

585
00:36:34,680 --> 00:36:37,080
I brought her here for peace of mind.

586
00:36:37,960 --> 00:36:39,480
But it's getting worse.

587
00:36:42,960 --> 00:36:44,559
Do you know what's the saddest part?

588
00:36:44,560 --> 00:36:45,560
What?

589
00:36:46,160 --> 00:36:48,200
She tries to be strong in front of me.

590
00:36:49,880 --> 00:36:51,560
And I feel useless.

591
00:36:52,160 --> 00:36:54,280
Because I'm not able to protect her.

592
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:00,879
What about that heart?

593
00:37:00,880 --> 00:37:02,479
Did you find out who did it?

594
00:37:02,480 --> 00:37:04,479
Not yet.

595
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:06,520
Your CCTV footage wasn't helpful.

596
00:37:10,400 --> 00:37:11,360
Adrean.

597
00:37:12,360 --> 00:37:13,640
Don't you think that...

598
00:37:15,720 --> 00:37:19,080
No, not possible. He's dead.

599
00:37:21,240 --> 00:37:22,560
Ridz.

600
00:37:23,080 --> 00:37:24,280
Where's Radwa?

601
00:37:24,880 --> 00:37:26,479
- No, Radwa's not with me.
- Okay.

602
00:37:26,480 --> 00:37:28,759
When I went to the kitchen
to look for her,

603
00:37:28,760 --> 00:37:30,719
Grandma said

604
00:37:30,720 --> 00:37:33,359
- Radwa argued with Aina.
- I seek forgiveness from God.

605
00:37:33,360 --> 00:37:34,840
Go and look for her now.

606
00:37:42,520 --> 00:37:43,800
An argument?

607
00:37:46,960 --> 00:37:47,960
You!

608
00:37:48,640 --> 00:37:52,080
You're desperate to marry him, right?
Confident you can give him kids?

609
00:37:53,680 --> 00:37:55,080
What's wrong with you?

610
00:37:56,080 --> 00:37:57,320
Radwa?

611
00:37:58,080 --> 00:38:00,239
Jamilah? Aina?

612
00:38:00,240 --> 00:38:02,239
What's wrong with all of you?

613
00:38:02,240 --> 00:38:05,039
- Enough!
- Well, ask this woman, Mom.

614
00:38:05,040 --> 00:38:05,960
Ask her!

615
00:38:07,320 --> 00:38:09,960
She won't be satisfied
until our family is destroyed!

616
00:38:10,520 --> 00:38:12,679
You should just die, mad woman.

617
00:38:12,680 --> 00:38:14,959
Your mother surely regrets
giving birth to you.

618
00:38:14,960 --> 00:38:18,320
That's right! You're right!

619
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:25,399
My mother regrets giving birth to me.

620
00:38:25,400 --> 00:38:27,999
My life is a burden to everyone.

621
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:29,520
I burden Grandma.

622
00:38:30,120 --> 00:38:32,640
I burden Mom and Ridz!

623
00:38:34,920 --> 00:38:37,240
Especially, you.

624
00:38:37,880 --> 00:38:40,079
You can't have Ridz as your son-in-law.

625
00:38:40,080 --> 00:38:42,959
You don't get to steal
his dad's wealth too, right?

626
00:38:42,960 --> 00:38:44,279
Insolent!

627
00:38:44,280 --> 00:38:46,200
Crazy!

628
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:56,120
Crazy woman!

629
00:38:56,640 --> 00:38:59,440
Darling, please.

630
00:39:01,400 --> 00:39:03,599
Radwa?

631
00:39:03,600 --> 00:39:06,119
Radwa, love.

632
00:39:06,120 --> 00:39:08,439
Please, put the knife down, love.

633
00:39:08,440 --> 00:39:09,959
I'm here, treasure.

634
00:39:09,960 --> 00:39:11,440
Put the knife down, please.

635
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:24,439
You must be disappointed in me, right?

636
00:39:24,440 --> 00:39:26,599
Because I have yet
to give you a grandchild.

637
00:39:26,600 --> 00:39:29,360
I didn't even think about that, love.

638
00:39:33,160 --> 00:39:34,759
Ridz.

639
00:39:34,760 --> 00:39:37,799
You must regret marrying a woman like me.

640
00:39:37,800 --> 00:39:39,559
No, darling. No.

641
00:39:39,560 --> 00:39:41,839
Radwa, all of us love you.

642
00:39:41,840 --> 00:39:43,640
That's a lie!

643
00:39:45,200 --> 00:39:46,160
You!

644
00:39:46,760 --> 00:39:48,439
You want him so bad, right?

645
00:39:48,440 --> 00:39:52,999
- Marry him!
- I won't marry anyone else but you.

646
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:55,959
- Why do you still want this mad woman?
- Just shut up!

647
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:58,039
She's my wife, not a mad woman!

648
00:39:58,040 --> 00:40:01,199
You'll never marry me!

649
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:02,960
Just shut up!

650
00:40:04,880 --> 00:40:06,479
You're desperate for kids, right?

651
00:40:06,480 --> 00:40:08,560
Just marry her!

652
00:40:09,160 --> 00:40:10,599
I know everything!

653
00:40:10,600 --> 00:40:12,999
I heard everything!

654
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:15,439
You misunderstood. I didn't even say that.

655
00:40:15,440 --> 00:40:16,959
Please, put the knife down.

656
00:40:16,960 --> 00:40:19,119
Please, I'm with you, darling.

657
00:40:19,120 --> 00:40:21,239
Shut up!

658
00:40:21,240 --> 00:40:23,800
Shut up, crazy!

659
00:40:29,840 --> 00:40:31,280
Oh my God.

660
00:40:34,920 --> 00:40:36,440
I'm sorry.

661
00:40:37,600 --> 00:40:39,920
I shouldn't have brought you
back to Grandma's house.

662
00:40:40,960 --> 00:40:42,240
I know.

663
00:40:44,200 --> 00:40:45,360
No.

664
00:40:47,480 --> 00:40:49,560
All this is my fault.

665
00:40:52,440 --> 00:40:53,440
I...

666
00:40:54,280 --> 00:40:55,800
am bad luck.

667
00:40:59,080 --> 00:41:00,600
Aina is right.

668
00:41:02,920 --> 00:41:04,639
We shouldn't have married anyway.

669
00:41:04,640 --> 00:41:06,239
Darling.

670
00:41:06,240 --> 00:41:08,240
Don't say that.

671
00:41:16,280 --> 00:41:18,080
Just a second.

672
00:41:24,440 --> 00:41:26,359
Darling, go upstairs now.

673
00:41:26,360 --> 00:41:27,959
Let me discuss with her.

674
00:41:27,960 --> 00:41:29,240
That is not necessary.

675
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:31,400
I want her to be present.

676
00:41:32,040 --> 00:41:34,600
Mom, can you let me
discuss with her first?

677
00:41:35,200 --> 00:41:38,719
want you to make a decision today.

678
00:41:38,720 --> 00:41:40,839
What's all this?

679
00:41:40,840 --> 00:41:43,080
What's going on?

680
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:49,519
Radwa.

681
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:52,039
I've come here to tell Thariq

682
00:41:52,040 --> 00:41:53,880
to divorce you.

683
00:41:55,760 --> 00:41:58,640
And marry Raudhah.

684
00:42:01,680 --> 00:42:05,360
{\an8}TO BE CONTINUED

685
00:42:11,240 --> 00:42:12,879
{\an8}<i>Have you ever heard</i>

686
00:42:12,880 --> 00:42:15,040
{\an8}that if we love something,

687
00:42:15,800 --> 00:42:17,520
{\an8}we have to let it go?

688
00:42:18,920 --> 00:42:22,799
{\an8}I want you to force your husband
to divorce you, okay?

689
00:42:22,800 --> 00:42:23,879
{\an8}Okay.

690
00:42:23,880 --> 00:42:26,239
{\an8}- Okay, good.
- Fine. I agree.

691
00:42:26,240 --> 00:42:28,439
{\an8}<i>But why the secrecy? Why?</i>

692
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:30,599
{\an8}<i>Can you not play the victim now?</i>

693
00:42:30,600 --> 00:42:32,920
{\an8}Who's being secretive?
You've been keeping a secret from me.

694
00:42:33,520 --> 00:42:35,960
{\an8}<i>When love turns to hate,</i>

695
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:38,720
{\an8}maybe only then can you let him go.

696
00:42:39,320 --> 00:42:41,119
{\an8}Divorce me.

697
00:42:41,120 --> 00:42:42,880
{\an8}Thariq Ridzuwan.

